article.headline: Greenwalt scores season-high 21 for Lady Raiders
article.linkText: Texas Tech overcomes sluggish start, Penn St.
article.story:
LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) -- Cisti Greenwalt scored a season-high 21 points and Texas Tech (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) used a strong finish to the first half in defeating Penn State 79-65 on Tuesday night.

The Lady Raiders (7-2) overcame a five-point deficit by outscoring the Lady Lions 11-1 during the final 8:06 of the half. Tech took control during the early stages of the second half.

Penn State (5-5) was led by Tanisha Wright with 19 points.

Chesley Dabbs added 13 points and LaToya Davis and Alesha Robertson 12 apiece for Tech. Jennifer Harris finished with 13 and Amanda Brown 12 for Penn State.

Brown converted a three-point play with just over eight minutes remaining in the first half to give the Lady Lions a 26-21 lead. But Penn State turned the ball over on six of its final eight possessions of the half, and the Lady Raiders took advantage of the miscues to seize control.

Dabbs hit a 3-pointer with 1:38 remaining before the half to give Tech the lead for good at 28-26. Brooke Baughman added a pair of free throws and threw a nice pass to Davis for a basket just before the buzzer to give Tech a 32-27 lead at the break.

Greenwalt hit a jump hook and baseline jumper around a short jumper by Erin Grant as Tech opened a 50-36 lead with 12:55 left in the game.

Robertson put it out of reach moments later with a 3-pointer from the right side of the key with 12:05 left as Tech took a 54-38 lead.

Penn State could get no closer than 12 points the rest of the way, pulling within 68-56 with 5:11 left. But the Lady Raiders pushed the lead to 15 in bouncing back from a one-point overtime loss to Virginia Tech on Sunday in Las Vegas.
